WEBVTT

00:02.792 --> 00:04.291
You were in the war,
weren't you?

00:04.583 --> 00:07.500
The way you hold your cigarette,
hiding the ember in your palm.

00:07.917 --> 00:09.125
I guess I'm still trying
not to give 'em

00:09.208 --> 00:10.250
something to shoot at.

00:11.166 --> 00:12.834
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:12.917 --> 00:15.083
An unspeakable act
was visited upon us.

00:15.458 --> 00:16.834
-(AGONIZED CRY)
-Friends of yours?

00:16.917 --> 00:18.208
Members of my church.

00:18.291 --> 00:19.834
The Radiant Assembly of God.

00:20.583 --> 00:23.291
PERRY MASON: Someone creeps in
Emily's house and nabs her kid?

00:23.709 --> 00:25.166
So you agree with the police.

00:25.250 --> 00:27.792
You think the Dodson's
had something to do with it.

00:28.250 --> 00:29.583
I'm not agreeing with anyone.

00:30.166 --> 00:31.458
It's queer from both sides.

00:32.125 --> 00:33.250
I'm gonna nail Dodson.

00:33.333 --> 00:34.959
Gotta know something stinks
around you.

00:35.291 --> 00:36.834
Why didn't you call the police?

00:36.917 --> 00:38.083
I didn't kidnap my son!

00:38.458 --> 00:40.166
DELLA STREET:
Someone stitched those eyes.

00:40.750 --> 00:41.834
MAN:
Worse thing you've ever seen.

00:42.458 --> 00:44.041
MATTHEW DODSON: None of this
was part of the plan.

00:44.125 --> 00:45.083
I should have run.

00:45.166 --> 00:47.125
Evening gentlemen,
sorry I'm late.

00:47.208 --> 00:48.291
Let's get this over with.

00:51.041 --> 00:52.125
(YELLS)

00:55.375 --> 00:56.959
This is a live one.

00:57.834 --> 00:58.959
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:06.917 --> 01:09.208
PERRY MASON: Fix bayonets!

01:09.291 --> 01:11.583
Fix bayonets!

01:11.667 --> 01:15.083
Fix bayonets. Let's go.
Watch your points.

01:15.166 --> 01:16.959
-Come on, make ready.
-(SOLDIER GROANS)

01:17.041 --> 01:19.083
-Look alive, stay alive.
-SOLDIER: Yes, sir.

01:19.166 --> 01:21.250
Yeah. Close in, close in.

01:21.333 --> 01:22.750
(BULLETS WHISTLING)

01:22.834 --> 01:24.166
Make ready.

01:25.375 --> 01:26.917
Make ready!

01:27.000 --> 01:28.333
SOLDIER: Get ready.

01:29.208 --> 01:31.542
(EXPLOSIONS)

01:36.000 --> 01:38.083
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

01:38.166 --> 01:39.625
Edendale!

01:39.709 --> 01:41.291
-(MCCAFFREY GROANS)
-(GUNFIRE)

01:41.375 --> 01:43.208
(EXPLOSIONS)

01:43.291 --> 01:44.792
(SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

01:44.875 --> 01:46.375
Hit the line!

01:46.458 --> 01:49.291
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

01:53.250 --> 01:56.458
-SOLDIER 2: Hit the line!
-(SOLDIER 3 SCREAMS)

01:56.542 --> 02:01.417
-(DISTORTED EXPLOSIONS)
-(PANTING)

02:03.291 --> 02:05.125
MASON: Come on!

02:05.208 --> 02:08.000
-SOLIDER 4: Follow me, boys!
-(GUNFIRE)

02:09.458 --> 02:10.750
(SOLDIER 5 YELPS)

02:12.583 --> 02:14.375
(EXPLOSIONS)

02:14.458 --> 02:15.875
(MASON GRUNTS)

02:16.875 --> 02:19.417
(BULLETS WHISTLING)

02:24.166 --> 02:26.625
(RECITES PRAYER QUIETLY)

02:26.709 --> 02:31.083
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:44.375 --> 02:46.208
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

02:54.917 --> 02:57.667
-FINKEL: Mason.
-MASON: Happy New Year.

02:57.750 --> 02:59.041
FINKEL: Says you.

02:59.709 --> 03:01.917
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC STOPS) ♪

03:05.375 --> 03:08.917
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

03:13.625 --> 03:15.875
Yeah. You wanted thread?

03:27.083 --> 03:28.458
There's thread.

03:32.875 --> 03:34.500
ALICE MCKEEGAN:
And I can imagine God,

03:34.583 --> 03:38.625
opening up his book of the
world and wondering to himself,

03:38.709 --> 03:41.208
"Who needs me most today?"

03:41.291 --> 03:46.208
And I can imagine his great hand
flipping the pages

03:46.291 --> 03:49.917
and stopping when he comes
to our city.

03:50.917 --> 03:54.709
It's a heathen's morning
in Los Angeles!

03:54.792 --> 03:57.709
From the gambling boats
off Santa Monica

03:57.792 --> 04:00.750
to the brothels on Broadway,

04:00.834 --> 04:04.375
they are tipping back
their bottles,

04:04.458 --> 04:06.583
rolling bones in the alley,

04:06.667 --> 04:11.500
cheating themselves
out of a life with Christ!

04:11.583 --> 04:13.792
-(AUDIENCE CHEERING)
-Liars!

04:14.250 --> 04:15.875
Thieves!

04:15.959 --> 04:18.500
-Fornicators!
-(CONGREGATION BOOS)

04:18.583 --> 04:21.959
Guests at the Devil's table,

04:22.041 --> 04:26.709
served a seven-course meal,
that feeds the body,

04:26.792 --> 04:28.709
but starves the soul.

04:28.792 --> 04:30.083
-(TRUMPET PLAYING)
-CONGREGATION: Amen!

04:30.166 --> 04:31.875
Isn't that right, Mother?

04:31.959 --> 04:34.333
It most certainly is,
Sister Alice.

04:35.291 --> 04:37.500
SISTER ALICE:
Brothers and Sisters,

04:37.583 --> 04:39.583
I've been given a calling,

04:39.667 --> 04:43.250
been given a voice
and gifted a set of lungs

04:43.333 --> 04:46.208
that would make Tarzan himself

04:46.291 --> 04:47.875
green with envy!

04:47.959 --> 04:49.250
♪ (ORGAN PLAYS) ♪

04:49.333 --> 04:51.291
No, no, no, no.
I'm not talking about you.

04:51.375 --> 04:54.250
You sit your hindquarters
back down.

04:54.333 --> 04:55.458
♪ (ORGAN PLAYS) ♪

04:55.542 --> 04:58.333
SISTER ALICE: It is my purpose
and privilege

04:58.417 --> 05:02.834
on this very first day
of the very new year...

05:04.208 --> 05:10.083
And I know it ain't been easy
getting here.

05:10.166 --> 05:12.709
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:12.792 --> 05:15.583
SISTER ALICE:
Now, we have all known

05:15.667 --> 05:18.709
our share of rough times.

05:20.208 --> 05:21.625
We all know what it's like

05:21.709 --> 05:24.000
to go to bed
with an empty stomach.

05:24.083 --> 05:26.333
CONGREGATION:
Amen!

05:26.417 --> 05:29.959
But Brothers and Sisters
of Radiant Light,

05:30.041 --> 05:33.959
and you listening at home
on your radio boxes,

05:34.041 --> 05:35.625
I am here to tell you

05:35.709 --> 05:38.583
right here and right now,

05:38.667 --> 05:42.375
there is another table
where you can sit

05:42.458 --> 05:44.917
with food from a kitchen

05:45.000 --> 05:49.041
where God does the cooking!

05:49.125 --> 05:53.375
And it, too,
serves seven courses!

05:53.458 --> 05:54.834
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

05:54.917 --> 05:57.333
SISTER ALICE:
I shout it, you shout it!

05:57.417 --> 05:59.208
-Chastity!
-CONGREGATION: Chastity!

05:59.291 --> 06:01.500
-Temperance!
-CONGREGATION: Temperance!

06:01.583 --> 06:03.417
-Charity!
-CONGREGATION: Charity!

06:03.500 --> 06:05.750
-SISTER ALICE: Diligence!
-CONGREGATION: Diligence!

06:05.834 --> 06:07.709
-SISTER ALICE: Patience!
-CONGREGATION: Patience!

06:07.792 --> 06:09.959
-Gratitude!
-CONGREGATION: Gratitude!

06:10.041 --> 06:14.333
-And humility!
-CONGREGATION: Humility!

06:14.417 --> 06:17.125
♪ ("LET'S GO ROUND
THE WALL" PLAYING) ♪

06:19.834 --> 06:22.542
CHOIR: ♪ Come on elders
Let's go around the wall ♪

06:22.625 --> 06:24.291
♪ That suits me ♪

06:24.375 --> 06:27.709
♪ Oh, come on elders
Let's go around the wall ♪

06:27.792 --> 06:29.542
♪ That suits me ♪

06:29.625 --> 06:31.834
ETHAN BROWN:
Oh, isn't she a wonder?

06:31.917 --> 06:32.959
A beacon?

06:33.041 --> 06:34.667
A beachhead for us sinners?

06:34.750 --> 06:36.792
Oh, give generously
if you can,

06:36.875 --> 06:40.458
give gloriously
for the radiance around you.

06:40.542 --> 06:41.750
Heed the words of our Sister,

06:41.834 --> 06:43.583
and dig as deep
into your pockets

06:43.667 --> 06:47.959
as God will allow you
on this great and good morning!

06:48.041 --> 06:50.917
Kick those sins out,
and welcome those virtues in!

06:51.000 --> 06:52.667
I wanna see those plates
piled so high,

06:52.750 --> 06:55.083
I want to see
those buckets brimming.

06:55.166 --> 06:56.417
Oh, are they here?

06:56.500 --> 06:57.917
Ah, yes,
they're waiting for you.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.000
The mother is very fragile...

07:00.083 --> 07:01.458
(SIGHS)

07:02.709 --> 07:03.750
You overcooked yourself.

07:03.834 --> 07:05.417
You want me to meet
with them privately?

07:05.500 --> 07:07.458
No, no, it has to be now.

07:07.542 --> 07:09.375
I just-- I have to catch
my breath.

07:10.667 --> 07:13.375
-I was good out there?
-(CHUCKLING) Oh, you were.

07:13.458 --> 07:15.500
Halfway to Heaven,
a mile from Moses.

07:21.458 --> 07:25.458
Sister Alice, this is Matthew
and Emily Dodson.

07:25.542 --> 07:28.083
I've been praying
every night and every morning

07:28.166 --> 07:29.542
since I heard, Miss Emily.

07:30.083 --> 07:31.417
Thank you, Sister.

07:32.250 --> 07:34.208
God is about all
we have right now.

07:34.291 --> 07:35.542
And He is with you.

07:40.291 --> 07:43.208
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

07:46.417 --> 07:48.083
(SISTER ALICE WHISPERS)
Come on, sit down.

07:50.458 --> 07:52.875
We've been in our home
for nearly a week.

07:52.959 --> 07:54.750
I thought it might be
a good idea

07:54.834 --> 07:56.917
to get Emily back here
to the Temple.

07:57.000 --> 07:59.667
Then we received your invitation
to come backstage.

07:59.750 --> 08:02.000
I saw your picture in the paper
and I said to my mother,

08:02.083 --> 08:05.417
"We must, must, must do
everything we can for them."

08:05.500 --> 08:09.208
-Didn't I say that, Mother?
-The very words, Sister.

08:09.291 --> 08:10.792
If you haven't
made arrangements,

08:10.875 --> 08:13.083
we'd like to offer the Temple
for Charlie's funeral.

08:14.709 --> 08:18.166
The Elders have offered
to pay for any and all expenses.

08:18.250 --> 08:20.917
-EMILY DODSON: Thank you.
-MATTHEW DODSON:
Thank you, Mr. Baggerly.

08:25.500 --> 08:27.166
STEVE HOLCOMB:
Mr. and Mrs. Dodson.

08:27.250 --> 08:29.583
-MATTHEW: Detective...
-HOLCOMB: Holcomb.

08:29.667 --> 08:32.208
Uh, excuse me for, uh...
interrupting,

08:32.291 --> 08:35.166
I need both of you
to come with me downtown.

08:35.250 --> 08:36.542
HERMAN BAGGERLY: What's this?

08:36.625 --> 08:39.208
That's good news.
We got a line-up to show you.

08:39.291 --> 08:41.625
But we need to go now.

08:41.709 --> 08:44.583
It's just a little legwork.
Do some digging on the car.

08:44.667 --> 08:46.333
Run down an alibi for Matthew.

08:46.417 --> 08:47.750
There-- there's good money here.

08:47.834 --> 08:51.166
You said that last time when
600 dollars turned into one.

08:51.250 --> 08:53.375
I'm-- I'm trying
to make it up to you.

08:53.458 --> 08:54.583
(CHILDREN GIGGLING)

08:54.667 --> 08:57.417
Hey! The hell did I say?
Never aim at the head.

08:57.500 --> 08:59.125
-I promise you, you'll get paid.
-Don't promise. Pay.

08:59.208 --> 09:01.583
Are you paying?
Say you're paying
'cause I got mouths to feed.

09:01.667 --> 09:02.542
E.B.'s paying.

09:02.625 --> 09:04.500
E.B.
E.B. thinks I'm a degenerate.

09:06.500 --> 09:09.834
And a good investigator.
He also thinks that.

09:09.917 --> 09:11.291
(CHILDREN GIGGLING)

09:11.375 --> 09:14.917
I-- I need the guy who taught me
half of what I know.

09:15.750 --> 09:17.792
Half? Try everything.

09:24.750 --> 09:26.458
All right. I have...

09:27.125 --> 09:29.959
twenty-three dollars.

09:30.041 --> 09:32.834
You can pad the expenses
as a sorry for the Chubby thing.

09:32.917 --> 09:34.083
-Ruthie.
-RUTHIE: What?

09:34.166 --> 09:36.208
Come take care of this,
they're running riot.

09:36.291 --> 09:39.000
-RUTHIE: I'm cooking, you do it.
-I'm in a business meeting.

09:48.834 --> 09:50.667
You wouldn't have an extra gun,
would you?

09:53.250 --> 09:54.875
Forget it.

09:54.959 --> 09:56.709
-MAN: Where you was last night?
-BOY: Ouch.

09:56.792 --> 09:59.709
Where were you?
Throwing all my stuff out there.

09:59.792 --> 10:01.041
LETITIA "GRANNY" JAMES:
Mm-hmm.

10:01.125 --> 10:03.417
You're throwing my stuff out
here on the street, Letitia?

10:03.500 --> 10:04.750
You lyin'.
I know what you're doing.

10:04.834 --> 10:06.166
GRANNY:
I ain't ask you to come around.

10:06.250 --> 10:07.500
What's going on here,
Miss James?

10:07.583 --> 10:08.917
None of your damn business.

10:09.000 --> 10:11.000
-He beating on you?
-DANIEL MADISON: Fuck y'all!

10:11.083 --> 10:14.291
He a walled-eyed son-of-a-bitch,
and I want him gone!

10:14.375 --> 10:17.625
This is my house, my house.

10:17.709 --> 10:19.834
I don't need him in my bed
no more.

10:21.375 --> 10:24.041
Daniel Madison.
Step on out now. Come on.

10:24.125 --> 10:25.959
-Fuck y'all.
-That won't help. Come on out.

10:26.041 --> 10:28.792
I don't take no shit
from nobody. Not from you.

10:28.875 --> 10:30.375
And not from this
old crow right here.

10:30.458 --> 10:33.125
You ain't nothing but shoeshine,
jabber, and Aqua Velva.

10:33.208 --> 10:35.458
DANIEL: Where was she at
last night? Ask her that.

10:35.542 --> 10:37.291
I ain't sitting around
watching your drunk ass

10:37.375 --> 10:38.750
all New Year's Eve.

10:40.208 --> 10:41.417
(GUN COCKS)

10:41.500 --> 10:43.083
Step back. Step back.

10:43.166 --> 10:45.250
-I'm gonna kill her.
-(ALL GASP)

10:45.333 --> 10:46.500
I'm gonna kill her right here.

10:46.583 --> 10:48.041
You ain't gonna do
nothing like that.

10:48.875 --> 10:50.041
Now, Daniel.

10:50.125 --> 10:51.709
Right now, we're just
having a little chat.

10:51.792 --> 10:53.125
You ain't no kinda police.

10:53.208 --> 10:56.291
-Badge say otherwise.
-Just dress you up, blood.

10:56.375 --> 10:58.333
Monkey on a leash
with a pop gun.

10:58.417 --> 11:00.834
I'm a proud man and she's been
running out on me.

11:00.917 --> 11:01.917
And I won't abide it.

11:02.000 --> 11:04.458
She went nowhere
but Zion Baptist last night.

11:04.542 --> 11:05.583
How you know that?

11:05.667 --> 11:07.000
'Cause Clara and I saw her
there.

11:07.083 --> 11:10.083
We all had punch,
and saw the year out.

11:10.166 --> 11:12.583
-Ain't that so, Miss James?
-Hmm.

11:12.667 --> 11:14.542
PAUL DRAKE: So why don't you
just give me that?

11:14.625 --> 11:17.375
Day for fresh starts.
Ain't nothing never been so bad.

11:17.458 --> 11:18.583
What you say?

11:19.417 --> 11:20.417
Come on.

11:29.375 --> 11:31.875
(HANDCUFFS CLINK)

11:37.834 --> 11:39.667
All right.

11:39.750 --> 11:41.959
If you don't mind,
just for one moment.

11:47.208 --> 11:50.875
Don't you ever
pull a gun on a police officer.

11:50.959 --> 11:53.208
-Motherfucker.
-Officer Drake. Officer Drake.

11:53.291 --> 11:55.709
Step on back now
unless you want some too.

11:55.792 --> 11:57.542
-(WHEEZING)
-The hell you playing at?

11:57.625 --> 11:59.458
Officer Drake,
there's something you gotta see.

12:06.583 --> 12:08.500
Straight on. Two-oh-six.

12:09.166 --> 12:10.709
This is as far as I go.

12:10.792 --> 12:13.125
I've been in there once,
I don't need to go in again.

12:14.625 --> 12:17.917
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

12:39.500 --> 12:42.166
(FLY BUZZING)

14:26.792 --> 14:29.166
Pulling him out of church,
for God's sake.

14:29.250 --> 14:32.166
There's a process, Detective.
You're to notify his counsel.

14:32.250 --> 14:35.041
-Well, you're here, aren't you?
-Notify beforehand.

14:35.125 --> 14:36.875
And where's this line-up
you promised?

14:36.959 --> 14:39.583
It's okay, Mr. Jonathan,
I wanna help.

14:39.667 --> 14:40.917
He wants to help.

14:41.458 --> 14:43.834
So, what do you think?

14:46.291 --> 14:48.125
It sure looks like my suitcase.

14:49.333 --> 14:52.375
I'd be certain except--
What's this here?

14:52.458 --> 14:53.834
It's a bullet hole.

14:53.917 --> 14:55.542
ELIAS BIRCHARD JONATHAN:
And how did this suitcase
come to be

14:55.625 --> 14:57.000
in your possession,
Detective?

14:57.083 --> 15:00.375
Newton Division found it
in an abandoned apartment.

15:00.458 --> 15:02.166
Along with a couple of stiffs.

15:03.583 --> 15:05.959
E.B. Jonathan,
you old so-and-so.

15:06.709 --> 15:08.583
You must be Matthew Dodson.

15:08.667 --> 15:10.583
Maynard Barnes.
Sorry I'm late.

15:10.667 --> 15:12.417
Mr. Barnes
is the District Attorney.

15:12.500 --> 15:14.083
Though I'm not sure
why he's here.

15:14.166 --> 15:16.709
(CHUCKLES) Similar interests,
I assume, E.B.

15:16.792 --> 15:19.625
But let me not interrupt.

15:19.709 --> 15:22.625
We were talking about
the Central Avenue stiffs.

15:22.709 --> 15:26.208
Yes, well, we believe these men,
murder victims it seems,

15:26.291 --> 15:28.792
were involved in the kidnapping

15:28.875 --> 15:30.959
and subsequent death
of your son.

15:31.041 --> 15:32.750
-That-- that's good, right?
-Involved?

15:32.834 --> 15:34.417
MAYNARD BARNES:
You have a gun, Mr. Dodson?

15:34.500 --> 15:35.583
-What?
-Yeah, sure.

15:35.667 --> 15:36.917
ENNIS: What kinda gun?

15:37.000 --> 15:38.542
Hold on, Matthew.

15:39.667 --> 15:41.500
What exactly are we doing here,
Maynard?

15:41.583 --> 15:43.166
Where were you the night
Charlie was taken,

15:43.250 --> 15:44.583
-Mr. Dodson?
-I told you guys.

15:44.667 --> 15:46.709
I was at the store,
totaling the receipts.

15:46.792 --> 15:48.291
E.B.: All right, let's go.

15:48.375 --> 15:49.792
BARNES: Sit down, E.B.

15:49.875 --> 15:51.291
Because you weren't working,
were you?

15:51.375 --> 15:53.625
E.B.: Bring us down here
under false pretenses

15:53.709 --> 15:55.625
for some goddamn ambush?

15:55.709 --> 15:57.500
-This is over.
-Sit the fuck down, gramps.

15:57.583 --> 15:58.917
Don't you speak to me like that.

15:59.000 --> 16:02.041
A patrol officer stopped by
your grocery twice that night

16:02.125 --> 16:04.458
to check on an open
transom window.

16:04.542 --> 16:05.834
And you weren't there!

16:05.917 --> 16:07.500
BARNES:
You were at home, Matthew.

16:07.583 --> 16:09.291
At home, the night
your son was taken.

16:09.375 --> 16:10.500
We have an eyewitness.

16:10.583 --> 16:12.083
This man is represented
by counsel.

16:12.166 --> 16:13.959
-He has nothing to say...
-BARNES: Saw him go
in the back door.

16:14.041 --> 16:16.250
-I wasn't there! I swear to God!
-BARNES: Saw him come out...

16:16.333 --> 16:17.875
...a minute later
with something in his arms.

16:17.959 --> 16:19.375
Something he could turn
into money.

16:19.458 --> 16:20.875
A quick score
to settle his debts,

16:20.959 --> 16:23.500
because you owe all over town,
don't you, Matthew?

16:23.583 --> 16:25.625
E.B.: I'm gonna lodge
a formal complaint.

16:25.709 --> 16:27.458
Badgering this man
with nothing but--

16:27.542 --> 16:28.959
I got motive. I got opportunity.

16:29.041 --> 16:30.166
E.B.: Yeah, you have...

16:31.291 --> 16:34.834
Maynard, you have
entirely a bucket of eels.

16:34.917 --> 16:36.291
(SCOFFS) Really?

16:36.375 --> 16:38.792
You're gonna tell a jury
that this man kidnapped his son

16:38.875 --> 16:40.250
because he had debts?

16:40.333 --> 16:42.500
And that his plan was
to extort money,

16:42.583 --> 16:45.667
which he clearly didn't have,
from himself?

16:45.750 --> 16:48.458
(LAUGHS) Please, be my guest.

16:48.542 --> 16:50.166
I'm gonna get
a two-dollar haircut

16:50.250 --> 16:53.166
so that I look good in
the papers laughing my ass off.

16:53.250 --> 16:55.333
Come on, Matthew.
Shame on all of you.

16:55.417 --> 16:58.542
That was the one thing
we couldn't quite figure.

16:58.625 --> 17:01.417
Why pull a snatch job
on a grocer's kid?

17:01.500 --> 17:03.500
And a hundred thousand?
Why so steep?

17:03.583 --> 17:04.834
(CHUCKLING) Makes no sense.

17:04.917 --> 17:06.333
Unless he knew
he had the money

17:06.417 --> 17:07.875
or knew that he could get
the money.

17:07.959 --> 17:10.458
Like from his rich father,
perhaps.

17:10.542 --> 17:12.125
But who'd know
a thing like that?

17:12.208 --> 17:14.667
I mean, such a well-kept secret.

17:15.834 --> 17:17.709
Wanna take a guess,
Mr. Dodson?

17:17.792 --> 17:19.792
Or should we call you
Mr. Baggerly?

17:22.208 --> 17:23.250
Baggerly?

17:24.291 --> 17:27.250
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:29.625 --> 17:30.959
Herman is your father?

17:33.667 --> 17:35.625
HOLCOMB: You're under arrest,
tough guy.

17:36.458 --> 17:37.542
Happy New Year.

17:37.625 --> 17:39.458
Might wanna hold off
on that haircut, E.B.

17:42.166 --> 17:43.875
-Now wait a minute.
-BARNES: Here, let me get that.

17:43.959 --> 17:45.625
Barnes, you're not getting...

17:45.709 --> 17:47.542
You're... (STUTTERS)

17:47.625 --> 17:49.625
-Barnes, this isn't--
-EMILY: Matthew?

17:49.709 --> 17:51.709
-This is not the way. Emily.
-EMILY: Matthew?

17:51.792 --> 17:53.542
-What is going on here?
-All right. Just calm down.

17:53.625 --> 17:55.000
-Matthew?
-I have to tell you

17:55.083 --> 17:56.750
-what's happened there...
-EMILY: Matthew?

17:56.834 --> 17:59.041
-What's-- Matthew.
-E.B.: ... it's nothing
we didn't expect.

17:59.125 --> 18:00.750
Matthew! Matthew!

18:00.834 --> 18:02.750
-REPORTER 1: He confessed?
-REPORTER 2: What's the charge?

18:02.834 --> 18:04.166
REPORTER 3:
You're nailing Dodson for it?

18:04.250 --> 18:06.000
REPORTER 4:
He's going down for it?

18:06.083 --> 18:07.750
Matthew Dodson is being held

18:07.834 --> 18:09.917
on conspiracy
kidnapping charges,

18:10.000 --> 18:12.041
proving once again that,
under my watch,

18:12.125 --> 18:15.000
criminal activities
will be quickly put down

18:15.083 --> 18:17.083
and the laws
energetically enforced

18:17.166 --> 18:19.375
to the benefit of all.
Take it.

18:20.166 --> 18:21.417
That's it.

18:21.500 --> 18:24.083
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

18:24.166 --> 18:26.125
REPORTER 1:
Dodson. Mr. Dodson.

18:26.208 --> 18:28.458
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

18:33.000 --> 18:34.333
A woman in Missouri.

18:35.834 --> 18:36.917
She lied to me.

18:38.583 --> 18:41.208
My fault certainly,
but I was lied to.

18:42.250 --> 18:43.583
I was a different man then.

18:45.000 --> 18:47.375
So Matthew is your son?

18:51.166 --> 18:52.875
He found me a few years ago.

18:55.333 --> 18:57.458
We made kind of an arrangement.

18:57.542 --> 18:59.417
He would give himself
to the Lord,

18:59.500 --> 19:01.959
I would provide the means
to resettle him here

19:02.041 --> 19:04.417
and start a business.

19:04.500 --> 19:07.583
He's a God-fearing boy now.
Not without his troubles.

19:07.667 --> 19:10.458
Like the kidnapping charge
he's up against?

19:10.542 --> 19:12.709
He would never get involved
with anything like that.

19:12.792 --> 19:15.709
Never? He sure lied
to the cops like a pro.

19:15.792 --> 19:18.000
Because he was engaged
in illegal gambling

19:18.083 --> 19:19.250
on the night in question.

19:19.333 --> 19:22.583
Given the circumstances,
I can understand his hesitation.

19:22.667 --> 19:24.333
They now have a witness
who saw him at home.

19:24.417 --> 19:26.750
And you're gonna find one
that saw him rolling dice.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.500
I assure you, Mr. Mason,

19:29.583 --> 19:32.000
my son is incapable
of harming anyone,

19:32.083 --> 19:33.834
let alone my grandson.

19:33.917 --> 19:35.125
Listen to this guy.

19:35.208 --> 19:36.959
Now, suddenly, it's "my son,"
"my grandson."

19:37.041 --> 19:38.333
Last week,
you didn't know Matthew

19:38.417 --> 19:40.583
-from the fucking gardener.
-Take it down a peg, boy-o.

19:40.667 --> 19:43.917
You waste your money,
Mr. Baggerly, if you lie to us.

19:44.667 --> 19:47.709
I did not lie. I do not lie.

19:47.792 --> 19:49.333
I told you
what you needed to know.

19:49.417 --> 19:51.709
You told us he was one
of your fellow parishioners

19:51.792 --> 19:52.917
in your church,

19:53.000 --> 19:54.583
not that you knocked up
his mother

19:54.667 --> 19:56.667
in between train whistles.

19:56.750 --> 20:01.041
And I was told that you were
a decorated serviceman.

20:01.125 --> 20:05.083
But actually you were discharged
with a blue ticket.

20:05.166 --> 20:08.583
A blue ticket is reserved
for undesirable servicemen.

20:09.250 --> 20:11.583
Homosexuals and Negroes.

20:11.667 --> 20:13.291
You're not Negro, are you?

20:20.458 --> 20:24.125
No, I'm a quarter Welsh
and queer only once.

20:26.834 --> 20:28.208
BAGGERLY:
I heard they called you

20:28.291 --> 20:30.125
the "Butcher of Montfaucon."

20:31.458 --> 20:33.667
Brought before
a military tribunal.

20:36.000 --> 20:37.917
Did I hear wrong, Mr. Mason?

20:39.834 --> 20:42.083
We tell one another
what we need to tell

20:42.166 --> 20:43.792
one another, do we not?

20:46.667 --> 20:47.959
E.B.: Son, why don't you get--

20:48.041 --> 20:49.834
I'm gonna double back
to the Dodsons'.

20:51.041 --> 20:52.959
Check out this witness
that suddenly remembers

20:53.041 --> 20:55.667
seeing Matthew in the alley.

21:03.583 --> 21:06.250
MASON: So I spoke to the guy,
their witness,

21:06.333 --> 21:09.000
a Mr. Kitt. You know him?

21:09.083 --> 21:11.792
EMILY:
No, I-- Maybe.

21:11.875 --> 21:14.000
One of your neighbors
just across the way there.

21:15.041 --> 21:16.667
I don't socialize much.

21:18.125 --> 21:19.208
No matter.

21:21.834 --> 21:25.291
He said he saw Matthew

21:25.375 --> 21:27.625
go down the side of the house

21:27.709 --> 21:29.083
when Charlie was taken.

21:29.166 --> 21:30.458
Which sounds worse than it is,

21:30.542 --> 21:33.709
'cause Mr. Kitt originally
told the police he saw "a man."

21:33.792 --> 21:37.834
Turned into "saw Matthew"
third time they leaned on him.

21:37.917 --> 21:40.375
I suppose that's good
that he wasn't sure.

21:44.208 --> 21:47.375
-Are you sure it wasn't Matthew?
-Of course I am.

21:49.542 --> 21:51.417
It's my job to ask
these questions.

21:51.500 --> 21:55.208
I'm only talking about
what might be possible.

21:59.208 --> 22:00.417
You, um...

22:01.375 --> 22:03.041
you fell asleep
in front of the fire...

22:04.792 --> 22:07.333
listening to the radio.

22:07.417 --> 22:10.291
EMILY: It was Rudy Vallee.
Fleischmann's Yeast Hour.

22:10.375 --> 22:12.458
I try to never miss it.

22:12.542 --> 22:15.250
(HALF-SINGS)
♪ When songbirds are singing ♪

22:15.333 --> 22:17.792
♪ Heigh-Ho, everybody
Heigh-Ho ♪

22:17.875 --> 22:19.667
EMILY: You like Rudy Vallee,
too?

22:19.750 --> 22:20.792
Not really.

22:20.875 --> 22:24.500
Just one of those things
that gets in your head,

22:24.583 --> 22:26.375
whether you want them there
or not.

22:29.542 --> 22:31.500
How are things
between you and Matthew?

22:31.583 --> 22:33.834
If you wanna push stories,
Mr. Mason,

22:33.917 --> 22:36.625
go on outside
and stand with the reporters.

22:36.709 --> 22:38.792
Stand out there,
and shout at my windows

22:38.875 --> 22:40.375
with the rest of them.

22:42.333 --> 22:45.083
Matthew would never...
hurt Charlie.

22:51.792 --> 22:54.792
Emily, whoever took your son
never meant to hurt him.

22:56.750 --> 22:58.291
They just wanted money.

22:58.375 --> 23:01.792
And something
went horribly wrong.

23:05.917 --> 23:07.458
Can I offer you a cigarette?

23:09.667 --> 23:11.959
EMILY: I'd prefer
you not smoke in here,

23:12.041 --> 23:13.500
if it's all the same to you.

23:15.208 --> 23:16.250
Of course.

23:27.208 --> 23:29.583
We only kept the females.

23:29.667 --> 23:32.500
I mean,
when we were having litters.

23:32.583 --> 23:35.792
Not that we pushed
the toms out, mind you.

23:35.875 --> 23:37.750
We're right Catholics.

23:37.834 --> 23:40.333
Mr. Trotter got a bucket
and drowned 'em.

23:40.417 --> 23:42.583
-It's the humane thing to do.
-Of course.

23:42.667 --> 23:43.750
(CAT MEOWS)

23:43.834 --> 23:45.417
Settle yourself, Sadie Mae!

23:45.500 --> 23:46.834
Did you see anything odd

23:46.917 --> 23:48.583
the night
Charlie disappeared?

23:48.667 --> 23:50.125
No. Sorry.

23:50.208 --> 23:52.250
No strangers?
No unfamiliar cars?

23:52.333 --> 23:55.959
Just the missus
gabbing away on the phone.

23:56.041 --> 23:58.917
You ask me,
the mister works too much.

23:59.000 --> 24:02.083
Poor girl talks on the phone
all night,

24:02.166 --> 24:05.834
just to have someone to talk to.
Kinda sad.

24:07.166 --> 24:09.083
You say she was on the phone
that night?

24:09.166 --> 24:10.667
MRS. TROTTER: Uh-huh.

24:13.291 --> 24:16.375
Look, she's at it again.

24:29.625 --> 24:30.959
(CAMERA CLICKS)

24:31.041 --> 24:34.625
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

24:34.709 --> 24:37.875
RUDY VALLE: Heigh-ho, everybody,
this is Rudy Vallee announcing

24:37.959 --> 24:42.208
and directing the recording
of our radio greetings.

24:42.291 --> 24:44.291
Heigh-ho, everybody, heigh-ho!

24:44.375 --> 24:47.333
♪ ("HEIGH-HO, EVERYBODY, HEIGH-
HO!" BY RUDY VALLEE PLAYING) ♪

24:57.709 --> 25:00.000
♪ When songbirds are singing ♪

25:00.083 --> 25:01.959
♪ Here's all they
Keep singing ♪

25:02.041 --> 25:06.834
♪"Heigh-Ho, everybody
Heigh-ho!" ♪

25:06.917 --> 25:08.959
♪ The breeze says
Each morning ♪

25:09.041 --> 25:11.500
♪ When daylight is dawning ♪

25:11.583 --> 25:16.166
♪ "Heigh-Ho, everybody
Heigh-ho!" ♪

25:16.250 --> 25:20.250
♪ Every star up in the sky
Looking down here below... ♪

25:21.709 --> 25:24.166
(GUNFIRE)

25:24.250 --> 25:26.709
(EXPLOSION)

25:27.375 --> 25:29.709
(INAUDIBLE)

25:34.041 --> 25:35.083
Go!

25:35.709 --> 25:37.959
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

25:39.875 --> 25:42.083
Come on, with me.

25:43.792 --> 25:45.875
-(GUNFIRE)
-(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

25:45.959 --> 25:47.542
-(BULLETS WHISTLING)
-(SOLDIER GRUNTS)

25:47.625 --> 25:50.000
-(EXPLOSIONS)
-(SOLDIERS GROANING)

25:53.417 --> 25:54.917
(SOLDIER 2 GROANS)

25:55.917 --> 25:57.834
(EXPLOSION)

26:00.375 --> 26:01.792
(BULLETS WHISTLING)

26:04.500 --> 26:05.792
(SOLDIER YELPS)

26:09.333 --> 26:11.000
(SOLDIER 2 YELPS, GROANS)

26:15.834 --> 26:18.500
(GRUNTING)

26:20.792 --> 26:25.083
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

26:25.166 --> 26:28.500
(BOTH GRUNTING, STRAINING)

26:30.166 --> 26:32.166
-(UNSHEATHES KNIFE)
-(SOLDIER GRUNTS)

26:37.333 --> 26:38.542
SOLDIER: Please, do it.

26:39.458 --> 26:40.500
Please.

26:42.166 --> 26:43.500
Please do it.

26:45.625 --> 26:48.083
Kill me. Please do it.

26:48.166 --> 26:51.500
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

26:54.417 --> 27:00.208
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

27:11.291 --> 27:13.625
MR. HARTE: Flowers,
obituary composition,

27:13.709 --> 27:16.542
casket and tombstone,
the inscriptions thereon.

27:16.625 --> 27:19.583
It is our business
to take on every detail

27:19.667 --> 27:21.542
so that you
and your husband...

27:23.417 --> 27:25.625
So that you and your family

27:25.709 --> 27:28.917
can concentrate
on the grieving at hand.

27:29.000 --> 27:32.000
Now, we have
a variety of caskets.

27:32.083 --> 27:33.417
Most are lined in satin,

27:33.500 --> 27:35.291
and the embroidery
is first rate

27:35.375 --> 27:36.959
from a seamstress in Oxnard.

27:37.041 --> 27:41.250
Well, any of these.
This one. This one.

27:41.333 --> 27:43.750
Ah. Might I suggest this one.

27:43.834 --> 27:46.500
Redwood casing,
blue interior satin,

27:46.583 --> 27:48.000
gold leaf on the pillowing

27:48.083 --> 27:49.375
-and it's available...
-I'm hungry.

27:49.458 --> 27:50.834
MR. HARTE:
...in an infant's sizing.

27:50.917 --> 27:52.959
I haven't eaten
since yesterday morning.

27:53.041 --> 27:54.875
E.B.: You know,
there's a swell diner

27:54.959 --> 27:56.375
down on Larchmont.

27:56.458 --> 27:59.959
Ms. Emily, why don't you
let me handle the affairs

28:00.041 --> 28:02.709
and Della can drive you
down there in my car.

28:04.583 --> 28:06.291
Gentlemen. Thank you.

28:10.250 --> 28:11.750
-Gentlemen?
-Yes.

28:15.542 --> 28:17.291
-REPORTER 1: Mrs. Dodson?
-REPORTER 2: Mrs. Dodson?

28:17.375 --> 28:19.625
REPORTER 3: Mrs. Dodson,
have you talked with your
husband since the arrest?

28:19.709 --> 28:21.417
REPORTER 4: Were you drinking
the night your husband--

28:21.500 --> 28:23.542
REPORTER 5: Do you think
your husband killed Charlie
himself?

28:23.625 --> 28:25.875
REPORTER 6: Mrs. Dodson,
is it going to be an open casket

28:25.959 --> 28:28.917
-or are you cremating the body?
-Sleep well at night, do ya?

28:29.000 --> 28:31.000
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

28:31.083 --> 28:33.125
DELLA STREET: Hey.
Get out of my way.

28:35.667 --> 28:38.959
♪ (JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

28:46.291 --> 28:48.834
Odd enough, finding two dead
white folks around this way.

28:48.917 --> 28:51.166
I mean, occasionally,
you find a stiff coal burner,

28:51.250 --> 28:53.375
a tea head,
but that's mostly about a knife

28:53.458 --> 28:54.542
stuck in them somewhere.

28:54.625 --> 28:58.083
Bullets, see, that's--
that's executive murder.

28:59.291 --> 29:01.000
That and the suitcase.

29:01.083 --> 29:02.583
And you connected
that off the briefings?

29:02.667 --> 29:04.333
DRAKE: Yes, sir.
And the hat. That sketch.

29:05.208 --> 29:08.083
Report here mentions
a blood trail.

29:08.166 --> 29:10.625
Yes, sir. Up the fire escape
to the roof.

29:11.750 --> 29:13.125
Leading to what?

29:14.208 --> 29:17.208
-Nothing.
-Nothing?

29:17.834 --> 29:18.834
Yes, sir.

29:20.375 --> 29:22.500
ENNIS: Could be
you got that wrong.

29:22.583 --> 29:26.375
Could be the trail starts
on the roof and leads down.

29:32.083 --> 29:33.834
Yes, sir. Could be.

29:33.917 --> 29:37.166
Ah. Only the,
uh, the drops of blood.

29:37.250 --> 29:39.834
The tail on the splash
points up those stairs.

29:43.500 --> 29:46.917
Wow, get a load
of this character.

29:48.208 --> 29:50.458
Officer Drake here
is a detective.

29:50.542 --> 29:52.375
Ain't that right, Officer Drake?

29:52.458 --> 29:55.125
You a detective like me
and Sergeant Ennis?

29:55.208 --> 29:56.625
No, sir. No.

29:56.709 --> 29:58.625
'Cause there are
no colored detectives.

29:58.709 --> 30:00.875
Hmm, maybe Officer Drake's
gonna be the first.

30:07.792 --> 30:11.458
(CLEARS THROAT) I personally
disagree with the policy.

30:11.542 --> 30:13.792
Had me a colored mammy
as a young-'un.

30:13.875 --> 30:16.250
Just as soon as work with
a colored detective as Ennis.

30:16.333 --> 30:19.583
But, uh... such is life.

30:22.041 --> 30:24.000
ENNIS:
This is some good work, Drake.

30:25.750 --> 30:26.750
Real good.

30:29.208 --> 30:31.375
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

30:50.583 --> 30:52.291
You haven't eaten very much.

30:54.291 --> 30:57.583
-Sorry.
-DELLA: No. It's okay.

30:57.667 --> 31:00.750
I look around lately,
thinking I forgot something.

31:02.583 --> 31:04.125
But there's nobody there to ask.

31:10.166 --> 31:12.417
E.B. will take care
of everything.

31:12.959 --> 31:14.709
Don't you worry.

31:14.792 --> 31:16.208
EMILY: Don't worry.

31:16.291 --> 31:18.959
We just went casket shopping
for my son.

31:21.875 --> 31:22.917
Excuse me.

31:24.792 --> 31:28.458
(RADIO PLAYS FAINTLY)

31:37.041 --> 31:40.041
-OPERATOR: Hold for your
connection, please.
-Thank you, Operator.

31:40.125 --> 31:43.333
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

31:55.417 --> 31:57.667
(SIGHS, SNIFFLES)

32:05.083 --> 32:08.333
♪ (JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

32:12.583 --> 32:14.458
Hello, Operator?
Operator?

32:14.542 --> 32:16.917
OPERATOR: Operator.
How may I direct your call?

32:17.000 --> 32:19.750
Uh, yeah. My wife was just
trying to, uh, reach her doctor

32:19.834 --> 32:21.542
but, well,
it seems she got cut off.

32:21.625 --> 32:23.959
OPERATOR: One moment, sir.
I'll try the line again.

32:24.041 --> 32:25.667
Thank you kindly, ma'am.

32:28.000 --> 32:29.083
OPERATOR: I'm sorry, sir.

32:29.166 --> 32:30.625
Your party doesn't seem
to be answering.

32:30.709 --> 32:32.625
No answer?
Well, this is real important.

32:32.709 --> 32:34.417
It's a medical situation,
you see.

32:35.375 --> 32:36.458
OPERATOR: I'm sorry, sir.

32:36.542 --> 32:38.125
Well, what number
are you trying?

32:38.208 --> 32:40.125
OPERATOR: Sierra 3-6517.

32:40.208 --> 32:42.291
MASON: Holy crow,
that's our own number.

32:42.375 --> 32:44.375
No wonder we're not home.
Thank you.

32:44.458 --> 32:46.166
Great coffee they got here, huh?

32:46.250 --> 32:47.792
Why the hell
are you following us?

32:47.875 --> 32:49.709
Well, E.B. wanted,
uh, to make sure,

32:49.792 --> 32:51.500
you know,
with all the reporters, that--

32:51.583 --> 32:53.333
You're a bad liar.
And a lousy tail.

32:53.417 --> 32:55.166
I don't have to explain shit
to you, Della.

32:55.250 --> 32:57.542
I'm-- I'm-- I'm working
the case. I'm doing my job.

33:00.125 --> 33:03.375
DELLA: Hey, kid,
let's get you home, okay?

33:06.750 --> 33:08.917
OPERATOR: Operator,
how may I direct your call?

33:09.000 --> 33:11.291
Uh, Boyle 2-3405.

33:11.375 --> 33:12.750
OPERATOR: One moment, sir.

33:13.917 --> 33:15.917
-DIANNE: Messenger Exchange.
-Dianne, it's me.

33:16.000 --> 33:17.333
DIANNE: Oh, he knows
my name today!

33:17.417 --> 33:19.792
Yes, I-- I-- Look, do you have
the reverse look-up handy?

33:19.875 --> 33:23.875
I need a name and an address.
Sierra 3-6517.

33:26.834 --> 33:29.041
Must feel good.
To be back.

33:30.000 --> 33:32.250
You look quite
the stalwart around here.

33:33.000 --> 33:34.542
I wouldn't say that.

33:34.625 --> 33:36.583
BARNES: I've seen the pictures,
heard some stories.

33:36.667 --> 33:39.583
(CHUCKLING)
A lot of stories, actually.

33:39.667 --> 33:41.208
Practically an original member.

33:41.291 --> 33:44.875
One of the "best young men
the city contained."

33:44.959 --> 33:48.583
Smaller city back in those days
and "best..."

33:49.917 --> 33:52.291
has always been a relative term.

33:53.458 --> 33:56.792
I'm sorry for, uh, catching you
out like that.

33:57.500 --> 33:59.375
It's a big case.
Lot of pressure.

33:59.458 --> 34:02.458
And there was
no disrespect intended.

34:02.542 --> 34:04.291
That's why I asked
to meet with you.

34:07.917 --> 34:10.291
Okay.
So let's hear it already.

34:11.458 --> 34:14.583
Dodson signs a confession.
I take hanging off the table.

34:14.667 --> 34:16.917
We pin the murder
on one of the dead guys.

34:17.959 --> 34:19.917
-That's tidy.
-BARNES: I like it.

34:20.000 --> 34:23.125
Mayor likes it.
The Newshawks are gonna love it.

34:23.208 --> 34:26.291
You took me once, Maynard.
It won't happen again.

34:26.375 --> 34:30.542
I relish, and that's not a word
I throw around casually,

34:30.625 --> 34:34.125
I truly relish the thought
of going into court with you.

34:34.208 --> 34:37.625
If you are Baggerly's friend,

34:37.709 --> 34:40.166
you should relish the chance
to save his son's life.

34:40.250 --> 34:42.083
Matthew Dodson is innocent.

34:42.166 --> 34:45.208
(CHUCKLES) Oh, come on,
I have an eyewitness, I have--

34:45.291 --> 34:47.166
My investigator
is currently looking

34:47.250 --> 34:48.625
into what little you have.

34:48.709 --> 34:51.208
This is a hanging case, E.B.,
not some gray-hair

34:51.291 --> 34:54.375
that wants to leave
her sweaters to a cat.

34:54.458 --> 34:57.917
Do yourself a favor,
and consider the possibility

34:58.000 --> 34:59.500
you may be
out of your depth.

35:00.792 --> 35:03.500
Stay as long as you want.

35:03.583 --> 35:06.667
Have another round.
On me.

35:12.667 --> 35:13.709
Gentlemen.

35:23.709 --> 35:26.000
BIRDY MCKEEGAN: Where are we
putting Mayor Carter?

35:26.083 --> 35:28.333
ELDER SEIDEL: On the house
right under the balcony lip.

35:28.417 --> 35:31.125
Oh, no. No, no, no, no.
That's not nearly close enough.

35:31.208 --> 35:34.542
Here, we'll put him on the--
on the aisle. (SIGHS)

35:34.625 --> 35:36.959
ELDER SEIDEL: I-- I believe
that's where you've sat

35:37.041 --> 35:39.208
Mr. Clark Gable,
Mother McKeegan.

35:39.291 --> 35:42.125
Well, he's a bread loaf
over six feet, isn't he?

35:42.208 --> 35:43.959
He is a tall man, yes, Mother.

35:44.041 --> 35:46.083
Well, we can't have the mayor
leaning and preening

35:46.166 --> 35:47.959
-trying to see the stage.
-ELDER BROWN: You'd have thought

35:48.041 --> 35:52.041
grim circumstances would have
driven everyone away, but...

35:52.125 --> 35:55.250
Well, who knew
we were even hosting the event.

35:55.333 --> 35:57.542
But here we are.
And we should do this

35:57.625 --> 35:59.917
as we do all things.
Best and better.

36:01.834 --> 36:06.250
Elder Brown, would Mrs. Brown
be willing to part with her seat

36:06.333 --> 36:09.542
to offer the mayor
a clear view of the stage?

36:13.750 --> 36:15.083
Whatever accommodates.

36:16.417 --> 36:18.625
I'll make sure
she gets a moment with Mr. Gable

36:18.709 --> 36:20.917
before we part to the cemetery.

36:21.000 --> 36:23.375
Perhaps it would be wise
to move the event

36:23.458 --> 36:26.792
directly to the cemetery,
considering.

36:28.083 --> 36:29.333
Considering what?

36:29.417 --> 36:31.709
A member's child
is being laid to rest.

36:31.792 --> 36:35.083
But... one is also being charged
with murder.

36:36.750 --> 36:38.500
HERMAN BAGGERLY:
Kidnapping. Not murder.

36:38.583 --> 36:41.500
And the police are in serious
error on that matter.

36:41.583 --> 36:44.458
ELDER BROWN: I merely wonder
if this is a light

36:44.542 --> 36:46.083
too bright for our church.

36:46.166 --> 36:48.125
BAGGERLY:
My son did not do this.

36:48.208 --> 36:51.542
He's a child of Christ's blood,
just like you and me.

36:51.625 --> 36:53.000
Do not let the sin of his birth,

36:53.083 --> 36:55.375
nor the fact that I kept
this shame from all of you...

36:55.458 --> 36:56.792
Do not let it blind you.

36:57.709 --> 36:59.417
SISTER ALICE:
Blessed are the mourners.

37:00.667 --> 37:03.291
Isn't that the truest thing
you ever heard?

37:05.583 --> 37:08.291
Mother, Brother Baggerly,
can I speak on that tomorrow?

37:08.375 --> 37:10.417
That sounds lovely, Sister.

37:12.625 --> 37:14.291
I'm sure
that'll bring great comfort

37:14.375 --> 37:15.792
to all those in attendance.

37:15.875 --> 37:19.125
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:44.166 --> 37:47.667
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

37:52.834 --> 37:54.000
(DOOR CREAKS)

37:54.083 --> 37:56.000
(CRICKET CHIRPING)

37:56.083 --> 37:59.166
(DOG BARKING)

38:27.125 --> 38:28.291
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

38:28.375 --> 38:30.417
MASON: Fuller Brush Man.
Get a handy new brush

38:30.500 --> 38:32.208
for just two minutes
of your time.

38:35.333 --> 38:38.542
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

38:50.417 --> 38:53.417
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

38:53.500 --> 38:57.041
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
CONTINUES) ♪

39:26.583 --> 39:27.875
MASON: That your car outside?

39:27.959 --> 39:31.458
'Cause I'd like to ask you
a few questions.

40:51.583 --> 40:53.709
(RADIO PLAYS DISTANTLY)

40:57.291 --> 40:58.500
CLARA DRAKE: What?

41:01.000 --> 41:02.250
DRAKE: It's work.

41:04.083 --> 41:05.959
Watch Commander say
I made a mistake.

41:06.041 --> 41:11.333
'Cept I didn't make no mistake.
'Cept he says I did. So.

41:11.417 --> 41:13.583
I had to change my report.

41:13.667 --> 41:15.583
-CLARA: This Joe Morton?
-Yeah.

41:15.667 --> 41:18.125
You say, "Joe Morton
dumber than a bag of hammers."

41:18.208 --> 41:20.709
That's 'cause he is dumber
than a bag of hammers.

41:20.792 --> 41:22.208
So why'd you change it?

41:23.208 --> 41:24.834
Baby, why do you think?

41:25.875 --> 41:26.875
Hmm.

41:31.208 --> 41:32.792
CLARA: Hmm.

41:32.875 --> 41:34.542
-Hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

41:34.625 --> 41:35.625
-Hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

41:35.709 --> 41:37.500
-Outta my face, cop.
-(CHUCKLES)

41:37.583 --> 41:40.375
That's Officer Drake
to you, Ms. Lip.

41:40.458 --> 41:41.458
Hmm.

41:41.542 --> 41:44.709
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

41:45.250 --> 41:47.583
(PANS CLATTERING)

43:40.166 --> 43:41.792
OFFICER COBB:
Hey, pal. No visitors

43:41.875 --> 43:43.750
-unless it's cleared downtown.
-MASON: Yeah. I work
for their attorney.

43:43.834 --> 43:45.000
OFFICER COBB: I don't care
who you work for,

43:45.083 --> 43:46.750
you get back in the truck.
Hey, stop right there.

43:46.834 --> 43:48.083
-Mrs. Dodson?
-Hey. Hey.

43:48.166 --> 43:49.834
-Emily?
-Hey, you feel that?

43:49.917 --> 43:51.250
-I will--
-Mr. Mason?

43:51.333 --> 43:53.458
See?
She knows me.

43:53.542 --> 43:55.458
-EMILY: What's going on?
-Be quiet.

43:55.542 --> 43:56.709
You're hurting me.

43:59.875 --> 44:01.250
MASON: Who's George Gannon?

44:02.709 --> 44:04.709
-George... Gannon?
-Who's George Gannon?

44:04.792 --> 44:07.291
-I don't know anyone named--
-Don't, don't, don't...

44:07.375 --> 44:09.750
-Don't do it.
-He's a friend from church.

44:09.834 --> 44:12.291
Do not-- Do not lie to me,
do not lie to me.

44:12.375 --> 44:13.542
Who's George?

44:17.208 --> 44:18.458
"My beautiful George,

44:18.542 --> 44:20.041
It's been three days
since we saw each other,

44:20.125 --> 44:21.458
but it feels
more like three years..."

44:21.542 --> 44:22.834
He's a friend from church.

44:22.917 --> 44:24.625
"Take me away, George.
To some island in the ocean.

44:24.709 --> 44:26.500
And set fire to the boat
that got us there..."

44:26.583 --> 44:28.250
Those aren't yours.

44:30.542 --> 44:32.166
MASON: "God must want us
to be together,

44:32.250 --> 44:33.959
or we wouldn't
be feeling this way.

44:34.041 --> 44:36.291
I love no one
more than you, Emily."

44:36.834 --> 44:39.375
(SOBS)

44:40.208 --> 44:43.875
-Where's George?
-George is dead.

44:45.417 --> 44:48.959
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:53.166 --> 44:54.250
No.

44:54.750 --> 44:55.750
No!

44:57.291 --> 45:00.125
(EMILY WAILS)

45:07.291 --> 45:09.291
(EMILY CONTINUES WAILING)

45:17.291 --> 45:18.375
MASON: No, she's lying!

45:18.458 --> 45:20.834
I gave her a chance
to come clean, she dithered.

45:20.917 --> 45:22.542
Now, she's letting her husband
swing for it.

45:22.625 --> 45:24.875
-(TELEPHONE RINGS)
-Hey, you took evidence
from a crime scene!

45:24.959 --> 45:26.542
You could lose
your license for this!

45:26.625 --> 45:28.250
-(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)
-They don't have to know
where we got them.

45:28.333 --> 45:29.291
It gets our client off.

45:29.375 --> 45:30.792
DELLA: And gets another client
the rope.

45:30.875 --> 45:33.375
E.B.: Are you gonna
answer that?

45:33.458 --> 45:37.125
The client is Herman Baggerly,
who's out a hundred thou,

45:37.208 --> 45:39.750
whose wife and legitimate kids
are gonna get humiliated.

45:39.834 --> 45:41.834
Yes. A lying dad,
with a bastard son,

45:41.917 --> 45:43.917
and a daughter-in-law
who's a goddamn cheat.

45:44.000 --> 45:46.083
-Hmm. The holy trinity.
-E.B.: You shut up.

45:46.166 --> 45:47.625
-He's a degenerate.
-See?

45:47.709 --> 45:48.917
He even used the word!

45:49.000 --> 45:51.291
No. Don't shut up.
Tell him what you got.

45:51.375 --> 45:52.667
I tracked down two chinks

45:52.750 --> 45:55.083
say they were in that dice
joint with Dodson on the night.

45:55.166 --> 45:57.250
I told you
to check out Matthew's alibi.

45:57.333 --> 45:59.083
He was too busy
following Emily and me.

45:59.166 --> 46:00.625
MASON: Yeah. Good thing I did.

46:00.709 --> 46:02.500
She had nothing to do
with Charlie's murder.

46:02.583 --> 46:04.041
Well, these letters
say different.

46:04.125 --> 46:06.875
These letters say
she had an affair. So what?

46:06.959 --> 46:08.208
You didn't spend the day
with her.

46:08.291 --> 46:10.417
The woman is broken.
I got a feeling, Chief.

46:10.500 --> 46:11.750
There's a guy on Vista Drive

46:11.834 --> 46:13.542
-with no feeling
in his fucking head...
-(TELEPHONE RINGS)

46:13.625 --> 46:15.000
...and Little Charlie
is about to get embalmed

46:15.083 --> 46:16.917
over at Harte and Hanna.
So, spare me the intuition.

46:17.000 --> 46:18.667
E.B.: Do I pay you
to answer the phone?

46:18.750 --> 46:20.000
Yes, I do.

46:20.917 --> 46:23.333
(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

46:24.625 --> 46:26.750
E.B. Jonathan's office.
How can I help you?

46:28.583 --> 46:31.959
Cops got it half right,
it's extortion gone way wrong.

46:32.041 --> 46:33.667
But it's not Matthew.
It's Emily

46:33.750 --> 46:36.291
and this guy George
and the hoods he got in with.

46:36.375 --> 46:38.125
The cops coached
the neighbor's statement.

46:38.208 --> 46:40.542
It was George Gannon
he saw in the alley that night.

46:40.625 --> 46:41.959
PETE STRICKLAND: I thought
you said

46:42.041 --> 46:44.000
George was on the phone,
distracting her.

46:47.333 --> 46:49.125
Yeah.
He-- he was.

46:49.208 --> 46:50.917
-How could he manage both?
-I don't know!

46:51.000 --> 46:52.875
Maybe he's one of the stiffs
of Central Ave!

46:52.959 --> 46:54.458
Pulling this
outta your ass, boy-o...

46:54.542 --> 46:55.959
Oh, that I agree with.

46:56.041 --> 46:59.583
And you, it's "E.B.
Jonathan and Associates"

46:59.667 --> 47:00.959
when you answer the phone!

47:01.041 --> 47:02.291
Haven't been associates
for six years!

47:02.375 --> 47:04.166
STRICKLAND: Ooh. You people
got some things to sort out.

47:04.250 --> 47:06.417
I don't reimburse
for whorehouses.

47:10.417 --> 47:12.917
What? I was tailing a guy.
I had to blend in!

47:13.000 --> 47:15.792
-(TELEPHONE RINGS)
-E.B.: Blend in...

47:15.875 --> 47:17.667
MASON: Look, George's place
was all wrong.

47:17.750 --> 47:20.333
A trumped-up suicide note?
I kill my partners,

47:20.417 --> 47:22.166
I burned the money,
I blow my head off,

47:22.250 --> 47:24.333
'cause woe is me,
I have a guilty conscience?

47:24.417 --> 47:26.041
You know who else has
a guilty conscience?

47:26.125 --> 47:27.917
Percy DuMott, sophisticated man
of distinction!

47:28.000 --> 47:29.291
Would you shut the fuck up?

47:29.375 --> 47:31.166
You're giving me migraines,
son.

47:31.250 --> 47:33.375
How am I supposed
to even introduce these?

47:33.458 --> 47:34.709
How do I get 'em?

47:34.792 --> 47:36.500
This is reasonable doubt
for Matthew.

47:36.583 --> 47:38.166
Infidelity is not murder.

47:38.250 --> 47:41.166
E.B.: Look, we gotta look
at what we got.

47:41.250 --> 47:44.083
Matthew's a gambler.
Emily's a cheat.

47:44.166 --> 47:46.166
Either of you think
they killed their kid?

47:46.250 --> 47:47.834
-No.
-I don't know.

47:47.917 --> 47:49.125
Not intentionally.

47:52.166 --> 47:53.709
I don't suppose
you could put these

47:53.792 --> 47:55.083
back where you found them?

47:56.458 --> 47:57.542
You had me call it in.

47:57.625 --> 47:59.291
Cops are probably
crawling already.

48:00.583 --> 48:02.542
E.B.: The letters stay here.

48:02.625 --> 48:05.333
We sit on them until I figure
the best way to use them.

48:05.417 --> 48:08.041
Everyone hear that?
Until I figure.

48:08.125 --> 48:10.250
Someone has to lead,
and that's me.

48:10.750 --> 48:13.458
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

48:15.375 --> 48:17.041
We're gonna need more phones.

48:17.125 --> 48:19.417
Or an answering service.

48:24.792 --> 48:27.583
E.B. Jonathan and Associates.

48:27.667 --> 48:30.208
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

48:30.291 --> 48:32.417
DELLA: Mr. Jonathan is in
a meeting at the moment.

48:32.500 --> 48:34.375
I can take a message.

48:34.458 --> 48:38.542
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
CONTINUES) ♪

48:48.333 --> 48:50.625
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

48:51.917 --> 48:54.125
(BABY CRYING)

48:54.208 --> 48:55.792
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

49:02.375 --> 49:03.667
We're ready.

49:08.750 --> 49:14.083
(CHOIR SINGING)

49:22.000 --> 49:23.458
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

49:23.542 --> 49:25.458
(CHOIR SINGING)
♪ Hallelujah ♪

49:25.542 --> 49:29.875
♪ Hallelujah ♪

49:57.291 --> 50:01.166
"Blessed are those who mourn,
for they will be comforted."

50:01.250 --> 50:04.875
CONGREGATION: Amen!
Praise be!

50:04.959 --> 50:07.291
SISTER ALICE: The words
of Jesus Christ Our Lord,

50:07.375 --> 50:09.250
from His Sermon on the Mount.

50:10.417 --> 50:13.250
There's another name
for that part of the good book,

50:14.583 --> 50:16.083
The Beatitudes.

50:17.333 --> 50:21.291
And it is a beautiful thought.

50:21.375 --> 50:25.667
"Blessed are those who mourn,
for they will be comforted."

50:25.750 --> 50:27.792
CONGREGATION: Amen!

50:32.750 --> 50:37.083
But how will Emily Dodson
be comforted?

50:42.291 --> 50:48.208
This glorious mother,
who birthed the child,

50:48.291 --> 50:50.750
who bathed the child,

50:50.834 --> 50:53.166
who fed the child
from her body,

50:53.250 --> 50:55.917
how do we,
Brothers and Sisters,

50:56.000 --> 50:57.917
provide comfort for her...

50:59.166 --> 51:01.875
when the child,
Charlie Dodson,

51:01.959 --> 51:05.333
lies in this very box
you see before me?

51:08.792 --> 51:10.750
I don't know if we can.

51:14.458 --> 51:17.000
Do not misunderstand me, Emily.

51:18.000 --> 51:20.000
You will not know
another friendless day

51:20.083 --> 51:21.458
for the rest of your life,

51:22.166 --> 51:24.709
and God as my witness,

51:24.792 --> 51:28.834
may this Temple crumble
to its very foundations

51:28.917 --> 51:30.542
if we fail you.

51:30.625 --> 51:33.166
CONGREGATION:
Yeah! Amen!

51:37.083 --> 51:39.500
I see new faces
down in the front.

51:42.166 --> 51:43.166
Men.

51:45.208 --> 51:47.834
The most powerful men
in our city.

51:49.041 --> 51:52.667
Given the best seats
in our loving home.

51:58.417 --> 52:03.166
And just as I can't be sure
that we can offer comfort

52:03.250 --> 52:05.709
to the mother in mourning,

52:05.792 --> 52:10.083
I can't be sure I'll ever see
you men under our roof again.

52:10.166 --> 52:14.667
So let me address you directly.

52:24.083 --> 52:28.667
The Devil put Charlie Dodson
in this box.

52:28.750 --> 52:29.792
CONGREGATION: Yes!

52:29.875 --> 52:31.667
SISTER ALICE:
He flew up from hell,

52:31.750 --> 52:33.417
walked to our streets,

52:33.500 --> 52:37.917
and laid his violent hand
on this child's head.

52:38.000 --> 52:40.917
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

52:41.917 --> 52:44.750
SISTER ALICE:
Beatitudes for the day at hand.

52:46.083 --> 52:48.375
Blessed be the police

52:48.458 --> 52:51.417
who will gather evidence
against the Devil.

52:51.500 --> 52:52.500
CONGREGATION: Yes!

52:52.583 --> 52:55.125
SISTER ALICE:
Blessed be the attorneys

52:55.208 --> 52:57.667
who will prosecute the Devil.

52:57.750 --> 52:58.834
CONGREGATION: Amen!

52:58.917 --> 53:03.333
Blessed be the jury
who will convict the Devil.

53:03.417 --> 53:07.125
Blessed be the judge
who will sentence the Devil.

53:07.208 --> 53:08.333
CONGREGATION: Yes!

53:08.417 --> 53:10.583
Blessed be the hangman

53:10.667 --> 53:13.208
who will snap
this Devil's neck.

53:13.291 --> 53:14.375
CONGREGATION: Yes!

53:14.458 --> 53:17.792
Blessed be the gravediggers
who will bury the Devil

53:17.875 --> 53:19.834
a thousand feet deep,

53:19.917 --> 53:24.417
and blessed be the worms
who will eat this Devil's flesh

53:24.500 --> 53:27.834
and disappear it
from the earth.

53:27.917 --> 53:30.041
(CONGREGATION CLAMORING)

53:30.125 --> 53:33.542
This is the work of the Lord.

53:33.625 --> 53:37.333
You do this work
for little Charlie Dodson.

53:37.417 --> 53:40.750
(CONGREGATION CLAMORS)

53:55.834 --> 54:01.208
(CHOIR SINGING)
♪ Immortal, Invisible ♪

54:01.291 --> 54:05.792
♪ God Only Wise ♪

54:05.875 --> 54:11.291
♪ In light inaccessible ♪

54:11.375 --> 54:15.333
♪ Hid from our eyes ♪

54:15.417 --> 54:17.083
♪ Most blessed... ♪

54:17.166 --> 54:19.792
What was that?

54:20.792 --> 54:25.500
(CHOIR SINGING)
♪ The Ancient of Days ♪

54:25.583 --> 54:30.500
♪ Almighty, victorious ♪

54:30.583 --> 54:35.917
♪ Of goodness and love ♪

54:36.000 --> 54:40.500
♪ To all life Thou givest ♪

54:40.583 --> 54:45.375
♪ To both great and small ♪

54:45.458 --> 54:49.834
♪ In all life Thou livest ♪

54:49.917 --> 54:54.625
♪ The true life of all ♪

54:54.709 --> 54:59.417
♪ We blossom and flourish ♪

54:59.500 --> 55:04.083
♪ As leaves on the tree ♪

55:04.166 --> 55:08.792
♪ And wither and perish ♪

55:08.875 --> 55:12.625
♪ But naught changeth Thee ♪

55:12.709 --> 55:15.291
Excuse me, officers.
Let go of...

55:15.375 --> 55:16.458
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

55:16.542 --> 55:18.083
Emily Dodson,
you're under arrest

55:18.166 --> 55:19.875
for the conspiracy kidnapping
of Charlie Dodson.

55:19.959 --> 55:21.291
-MAN: No.
-Come with us, ma'am.

55:21.375 --> 55:22.625
DELLA: No.
Let go of her!

55:22.709 --> 55:24.667
-EMILY: No. No. No.
